content:
You can add a formula that calculates values relative to a parent or peer grouping in a Lightning report. PARENTGROUPVAL calculates values relative to a parent grouping and PREVGROUPVAL calculates values relative to a peer grouping.

To create this formula:

* Select Add Summary Formula from the Columns section in the report builder.
* Enter a column name, select the formula output type, and select Functions.
* Choose PARENTGROUPVAL or PREVGROUPVAL, then select a specific grouping or groupings in the Display panel.
* In the Function panel, select the grouping or groupings to use in the function.
* Click Insert to add the function with selected parameters.
* Add other parameters, functions, and operators as needed.
* Validate the formula and click Apply to close the formula builder and add the summary formula column to the report.
title: Calculating Values with Parent or Peer Group Formulas
